              "name": "One Action",
              "subtype": "action_type",
              "type": "stat_block_section"
            },
            "effect": "The stormdrinker rings its bell, signaling Tumbo to bite him once. (Multiple bites don't stack their effects on the stormdrinker.) The stormdrinker can't use this ability when it doesn't have its bell, such as if it is Disarmed.",
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "Disarmed",
                "aonid": 2383,
                "game-obj": "Actions",
                "name": "Disarmed",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Ring Bell",
            "requirement": "The stormdrinker is carrying a bell",
            "subtype": "ability",
            "traits": [
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 16,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Auditory",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 453,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
                "type": "trait"
              }
            ],
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
          "name": "Ring Bell",
          "offensive_action_type": "ability",
          "subtype": "offensive_action",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
